<BaseLayout title="Contact | FreelancePricingCalc" description="Contact FreelancePricingCalc with questions, corrections, or feedback about freelance rate calculations.">
  <h1>Contact Us</h1>

  <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
  <p>We welcome questions, feedback, and correction requests. If you've spotted an error in our tax data, a methodology issue, or an outdated market rate benchmark, please let us know. Keeping our data accurate is a priority.</p>

  <p>Email us at: <strong>hey@theclicklab.agency</strong></p>

  <h2>What We Can and Cannot Help With</h2>
  <p>FreelancePricingCalc is an informational resource. We are not accountants, financial advisors, or tax professionals, and we cannot advise on your specific tax situation, business structure, or pricing strategy. Nothing communicated to us by email constitutes financial or tax advice or creates any advisory relationship.</p>
  <p>For specific tax guidance — quarterly estimated payments, home office deductions, retirement plan options, QBI deduction eligibility — consult a qualified CPA or Enrolled Agent who works with self-employed individuals. For business structure questions (LLC vs. S-corp vs. sole proprietorship), consult a CPA or business attorney. Good tax advice typically pays for itself many times over for independent contractors.</p>

  <h2>Data Updates</h2>
  <p>IRS tax brackets and self-employment tax thresholds are updated annually. If you believe our tax data is out of date, please email us with a citation to the current IRS publication. We'll verify and update promptly.</p>

  <h2>Response Times</h2>
  <p>We aim to respond within 3–5 business days. We cannot guarantee responses to every inquiry, particularly situation-specific questions we're not in a position to answer.</p>

  <p><em>Informational only. Not professional advice.</em></p>
</BaseLayout>
